Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art showing two spiral shapes with pecked grooves, linked by a curved pecked line. That on the bottom left is larger and radiates (?) clockwise, that on the top right is smaller and radiates anticlockwise. Surrounding the engravings on the rock are several unidentified archaeological artefacts from the surrounding area. Western Desert, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
